.TH "pci_disable_link_state" 9 "pci_disable_link_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_disable_link_state \- Disable device's link state, so the link will never enter specific states. Note that if the BIOS didn't grant ASPM control to the OS, this does nothing because we can't touch the LNKCTL register. Returns 0 or a negative errno.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_disable_link_state
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device
.IP "state" 12
ASPM link state to disable
